biblScope\">50.14</biblScope></bibl>, cf. Ps.-<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Luc.\">Luc.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Philopatr.\">Philopatr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">26</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"3\" id=\"n93058.2\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> of a wound or sore, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἕλκος σεσηρὸς καὶ ἐκπεπλιγμένον</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">gaping</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0627.tlg009.perseus-grc1:32\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hp.\">Hp.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Fract.\">Fract.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">32</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0719.tlg003.perseus-grc1:2:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Aret.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ CA\">CA</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.2</biblScope> </bibl>; also <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ς. χάσμημα</foreign>, of a metrical hiatus, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001:840:43\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eust.\">Eust.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">840.43</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}